\" data-file-width=\"512\" data-file-height=\"399\" /></a></div></td><td class=\"mbox-text\"><div class=\"mbox-text-span\">This <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Biographies_of_living_persons\" title=\"Wikipedia:Biographies of living persons\">biography of a living person</a> <b>relies too much on <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Verifiability\" title=\"Wikipedia:Verifiability\">references</a> to <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Biographies_of_living_persons#Misuse_of_primary_sources\" title=\"Wikipedia:Biographies of living persons\">primary sources</a></b>.<span class=\"hide-when-compact\"> Please help by adding <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:No_original_research#Primary,_secondary_and_tertiary_sources\" title=\"Wikipedia:No original research\">secondary or tertiary sources</a>. Contentious material about living persons that is unsourced or poorly sourced <b>must be removed immediately</b>, especially if potentially <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Libel\" title=\"Wikipedia:Libel\">libelous</a> or harmful.</span>  <small><i>(November 2010)</i></small><small class=\"hide-when-compact\"><i> (<a href=\"/wiki/Help:Maintenance_template_removal\" title=\"Help:Maintenance template removal\">Learn how and when to remove this template message</a>)</i></small></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<table class=\"plainlinks metadata ambox ambox-content ambox-BLP_sources\" role=\"presentation\"><tbody><tr><td class=\"mbox-image\"><div style=\"width:52px\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b4/Ambox_important.svg/40px-Ambox_important.svg.png\" width=\"40\" height=\"40\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b4/Ambox_important.svg/60px-Ambox_important.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b4/Ambox_important.svg/80px-Ambox_important.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"40\" data-file-height=\"40\" /></div></td><td class=\"mbox-text\"><div class=\"mbox-text-span\">This <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Biographies_of_living_persons\" title=\"Wikipedia:Biographies of living persons\">biography of a living person</a> <b>needs additional <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Citing_sources\" title=\"Wikipedia:Citing sources\">citations</a> for <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Verifiability\" title=\"Wikipedia:Verifiability\">verification</a></b>.<span class=\"hide-when-compact\"> Please help by adding <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Identifying_reliable_sources\" title=\"Wikipedia:Identifying reliable sources\">reliable sources</a>. Contentious material about living persons that is unsourced or poorly sourced <b>must be removed immediately</b>, especially if potentially <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Libel\" title=\"Wikipedia:Libel\">libelous</a> or harmful.</span>  <small><i>(November 2010)</i></small><small class=\"hide-when-compact\"><i> (<a href=\"/wiki/Help:Maintenance_template_removal\" title=\"Help:Maintenance template removal\">Learn how and when to remove this template message</a>)</i></small></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n    </div>\n</div><small class=\"hide-when-compact\"><i> (<a href=\"/wiki/Help:Maintenance_template_removal\" title=\"Help:Maintenance template removal\">Learn how and when to remove this template message</a>)</i></small></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p class=\"mw-empty-elt\">\n\n</p><p><b>Robin Cohen</b> (born 1944) is a social scientist working in the fields of globalisation, migration and diaspora studies. He is Emeritus Professor of Development Studies and former Director of the International Migration Institute, <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Oxford\" title=\"University of Oxford\">University of Oxford</a>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Career\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Career</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Intellectual_contribution\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Intellectual contribution</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Bibliography_of_major_works\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Bibliography of major works</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Career\">Career</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Robin_Cohen&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Career\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Robin Cohen was born in <a href=\"/wiki/Johannesburg,_South_Africa\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Johannesburg, South Africa\">Johannesburg, South Africa</a>. He left in 1964, returning to the country for three years in the post-Mandela period, when he served as Dean of Humanities at the <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Cape_Town\" title=\"University of Cape Town\">University of Cape Town</a> (2001\u201304). He has held appointments at the universities of <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Ibadan\" title=\"University of Ibadan\">Ibadan</a>, Nigeria (1967\u201369), <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Birmingham\" title=\"University of Birmingham\">Birmingham</a>, UK (1969\u201377), the <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_the_West_Indies\" title=\"University of the West Indies\">West Indies</a> (Professor of Sociology, 1977-9), <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Warwick\" title=\"University of Warwick\">Warwick</a>, UK (Professor of Sociology, 1979\u20132006) and <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Oxford\" title=\"University of Oxford\">Oxford</a> (2006\u2013). He is former director of the International Migration Institute which forms part of the <a href=\"/wiki/Oxford_Martin_School\" title=\"Oxford Martin School\">Oxford Martin School</a>. Cohen was principal investigator on the Oxford Diasporas Programme,<sup id=\"cite_ref-ox_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-ox-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> funded by the <a href=\"/wiki/Leverhulme_Trust\" title=\"Leverhulme Trust\">Leverhulme Trust</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Intellectual_contribution\">Intellectual contribution</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Robin_Cohen&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Intellectual contribution\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Robin Cohen's doctoral work was published as <i>Labour and politics in Nigeria</i> (1974).<sup id=\"cite_ref-google_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-google-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> There followed collaborative work on labour movements and labour history in other parts of Africa. However, his interest and expertise in labour developed into a wider project about the continuing significance of the movement of people across national boundaries and the problems to which this has given rise in very many parts of the world. In <i>The new Helots</i> (1987),<sup id=\"cite_ref-google2_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-google2-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> he suggested that Marx had underestimated the continuing salience of migrant labour, a feature that allowed capitalism to thrive and thereby evade the fundamental confrontation between worker and employer that Marx predicted.\n</p><p>Cohen made a number of other contributions to the field of migration studies by giving new understandings to key contested concepts such as diaspora and borders, citizens and denizens, and collective or national identity. In <i>Frontiers of identity</i>, (1994)<sup id=\"cite_ref-google3_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-google3-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> he argued that 'fuzzy' frontiers within the UK and between Britain, the Commonwealth, and the wider world create a particular ambiguous notion of 'Britishness'. His most influential work, <i>Global diasporas</i>, (1997, with subsequent editions and translations)<sup id=\"cite_ref-google4_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-google4-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> continued his analysis of the relationship between identity and migration. Through the use of typlogies, comparisons and suggestive lists of shared characteristics, Cohen was able to employ the ancient concept of diaspora to enrich the study of present-day transnational migrant flows.<sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> Along with <a href=\"/wiki/James_Clifford_(historian)\" title=\"James Clifford (historian)\">James Clifford</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/William_Safran\" title=\"William Safran\">William Safran</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Paul_Gilroy\" title=\"Paul Gilroy\">Paul Gilroy</a> and Khachig T\u00f6l\u00f6lyan, Cohen can be considered one of the founding figures of contemporary <a href=\"/wiki/Diaspora_studies\" title=\"Diaspora studies\">diaspora studies</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Bibliography_of_major_works\">Bibliography of major works</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Robin_Cohen&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Bibliography of major works\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>2006 <i>Migration and its enemies: global capital, migrant labour and the nation state</i>, Aldershot: Ashgate.\n</p><p>2000 <i>Global sociology</i> (with Paul Kennedy), Basingstoke: Macmillan; New York: New York University Press. Basingstoke: Palgrave. Reprinted 2001, 2002, 2004. Japanese translations 2003. Second expanded and revised edition March 2007. NYUP, September 2007. Revised edition 2013.\n</p><p>1997 <i>Global diasporas: an introduction</i>, London: UCL Press &amp; Seattle: University of Washington Press. Reprinted 1999, 2000. Reprinted 2001, Palgrave. Japanese translations (Tokyo: Akahi Shoton, 2001 and 2013) by Komai Hiroshi. Greek translation, with new preface, Athens, 2003. Revised second edition, London &amp; New York: Routledge, 2008.\n</p><p>1994 <i>Frontiers of identity: the British and the others</i>, London: Longman &amp; New York: Addison Wesley.\n</p><p>1991 <i>Contested domains: debates in international labour studies</i>, London: Zed Press.\n</p><p>1987 <i>The new Helots: migrants in the international division of labour</i>, Aldershot: Avebury/Gower Publishing Group; paperback edition, Gower, 1988; Japanese translation, 1989; reprinted 1993, 2003.\n</p><p>1986 <i>Endgame in South Africa: the changing ideology and social structure of South Africa</i>, Paris: UNESCO Press &amp; London: James Curry; German edition under the title <i>Endspiel S\u00fcdafrika: Eine Anatomie der Apartheid</i>, Translated by Ulf Dammann, with a Foreword by Jean Ziegler, Berlin: Rotbuch Verlag, 1987; US edition, New York: Africa World Press, 1988.\n</p><p>1974 <i>Labour and politics in Nigeria: 1945\u201371</i>, London: Heinemann Education Books &amp; New York: Holmes &amp; Meier/Africana Publishing Corporation. New edition 1982.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Robin_Cohen&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist columns references-column-width\" style=\"-moz-column-width: 30em; -webkit-column-width: 30em; column-width: 30em; list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-ox-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-ox_1-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.migration.ox.ac.uk/odp/\">\"Oxford Diasporas Programme &#124; Exploring migrants' networks and experiences\"</a>. migration.ox.ac.uk<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">8 January</span> 2017</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Oxford+Diasporas+Programme+%26%23124%3B+Exploring+migrants%27+networks+and+experiences&amp;rft.pub=migration.ox.ac.uk&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.migration.ox.ac.uk%2Fodp%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ARobin+Cohen\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-google-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-google_2-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Cohen, R. (1974). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=m9S6AAAAIAAJ\"><i>Labour and politics in Nigeria, 1945-71</i></a>. Heinemann<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">8 January</span> 2017</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Labour+and+politics+in+Nigeria%2C+1945-71&amp;rft.pub=Heinemann&amp;rft.date=1974&amp;rft.au=Cohen%2C+R.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.co.uk%2Fbooks%3Fid%3Dm9S6AAAAIAAJ&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ARobin+Cohen\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-google2-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-google2_3-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Cohen, R. (1987). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=SXsFAQAAIAAJ\"><i>The New Helots: Migrants in the International Division of Labour</i></a>. Avebury. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780566009327\" title=\"Special:BookSources/9780566009327\">9780566009327</a><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">8 January</span> 2017</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+New+Helots%3A+Migrants+in+the+International+Division+of+Labour&amp;rft.pub=Avebury&amp;rft.date=1987&amp;rft.isbn=9780566009327&amp;rft.au=Cohen%2C+R.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.co.uk%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DSXsFAQAAIAAJ&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ARobin+Cohen\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-google3-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-google3_4-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Cohen, R. (1994). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=tVRnAAAAMAAJ\"><i>Frontiers of Identity: The British and the Others</i></a>. Longman. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780582245761\" title=\"Special:BookSources/9780582245761\">9780582245761</a><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">8 January</span> 2017</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Frontiers+of+Identity%3A+The+British+and+the+Others&amp;rft.pub=Longman&amp;rft.date=1994&amp;rft.isbn=9780582245761&amp;rft.au=Cohen%2C+R.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.co.uk%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DtVRnAAAAMAAJ&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ARobin+Cohen\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-google4-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-google4_5-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Cohen, R. (2008). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=1tMICnlZ7fwC\"><i>Global Diasporas: An Introduction</i></a>. Taylor &amp; Francis. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780203928943\" title=\"Special:BookSources/9780203928943\">9780203928943</a><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">8 January</span> 2017</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Global+Diasporas%3A+An+Introduction&amp;rft.pub=Taylor+%26+Francis&amp;rft.date=2008&amp;rft.isbn=9780203928943&amp;rft.au=Cohen%2C+R.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.co.uk%2Fbooks%3Fid%3D1tMICnlZ7fwC&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ARobin+Cohen\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-6\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://andrewblackman.net/2010/04/global-diasporas-an-introduction-by-robin-cohen/\">\u201cGlobal Diasporas: An Introduction\u201d by Robin Cohen</a>. Andrew Blackman (16 April 2010). Retrieved on 13 November 2010.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_links\">External links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span